  "title": "🐾 Dog Groomer / Pet Groomer | Outram | Basic from $3,000 + Commission + AWS + Bonus",
  "description": "<p>Join a <strong>modern, Nordic-style pet grooming salon</strong> that believes in low-stress grooming and top-tier pet care!</p>\n<h3>✂️ <strong>What You’ll Do</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Perform <strong>full &amp; basic grooming</strong>, spa treatments, and medicated baths.</li>\n  <li>Conduct <strong>health checks</strong> and advise pet owners on suitable services.</li>\n  <li>Maintain <strong>high hygiene and safety standards</strong> in the grooming area.</li>\n  <li>Use <strong>premium tools and ergonomic equipment</strong> (Nanobubble Spa System).</li>\n  <li>Ensure pets enjoy a <strong>comfortable, low-stress experience</strong>.</li>\n  <li>Upsell grooming add-ons and pet-care products.</li>\n  <li>Work collaboratively in a <strong>friendly, professional salon team</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>🐕 <strong>What We’re Looking For</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>SKC Class C Certificate</strong> or higher (Class B/A preferred) / equivalent international grooming certification.</li>\n  <li><strong>Minimum 2 years</strong> of independent grooming experience.</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of <strong>low-stress handling techniques</strong>.</li>\n  <li>Patient, compassionate, and genuinely love animals.</li>\n  <li>Confident in communicating with clients and presenting grooming styles.</li>\n  <li>Able to work <strong>weekends (Sat &amp; Sun)</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>🕒 <strong>Working Hours &amp; Benefits</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>5.5 days/week</strong>, approx. <em>10:00 AM – 7:00 PM</em></li>\n  <li><strong>1.5 weekday off</strong> (roster-based)</li>\n  <li><strong>Commission:</strong>15% per grooming service<br>\n5% on upsells (e.g. spa, treatments)<br>\n</li>\n  <li><strong>AWS + Performance Bonus</strong></li>\n  <li><strong>Annual Leave:</strong> 7 days (increase +1 day per year)</li>\n  <li>Clean, pet-friendly environment with premium tools and supportive colleagues</li>\n</ul>\n<p>🐶 <strong>Requirements:</strong> Singaporean / PR, Chinese-speaking preferred, need to communicate with Chinese speaking associates.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>EA Personnel Name: Jabez Wong<br>\nEA Personnel No: R1762582<br>\nEA License No: 23C1703</p>",
